question name: How many battle deaths will ACLED record in Sudan in August 2017?
question description: The Armed Conflict Location and Event Dataset (ACLED) summarizes press reports on conflict and protest events in Africa and parts of Asia. Outcome will be determined by "The Realtime August 2017 All Africa File" found on the Realtime Data Page ( http://www.acleddata.com/data/realtime-data/ ). The count of battle deaths for August 2017 are obtained by summing the 'FATALITIES’ column for events in which the 'COUNTRY’ is: Sudan; 'EVENT_TYPE’ is: Battle-Government regains territory, Battle-No change of territory, or Battle-Non-state actor overtakes territory; and 'EVENT_DATE' is in August 2017. The question will be suspended on 31 August 2017 and resolved using data retrieved mid-September 2017.

question name: How many UN member states will sign the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons before 1 November 2017?
question description: In July 2017, a UN conference negotiated the text for the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons (http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=57139#.WXT5i4opBTZ, https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2017/07/17/the-u-n-just-passed-a-treaty-outlawing-nuclear-weapons-that-actually-matters/?utm_term=.1044e36e1f48). Starting on 20 September 2017 at the UN General Assembly, any UN member state can sign it (https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/07/world/americas/united-nations-nuclear-weapons-prohibition-destruction-global-treaty.html?mcubz=2).

question name: What will be the approval rate for Japan’s cabinet in NHK’s monthly survey in September 2017?

question name: How many earthquakes of magnitude 5 or stronger will occur worldwide in October 2017?
question description: This question will be resolved using the United States Geological Survey (USGS)’s Earthquake Catalog (https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/search/).  The relevant data can be found by setting the Magnitude to a Custom Minimum equal to the magnitude of interest; setting a Custom Date & Time of ‘Start’ to the first day of the month of interest and ‘End' to the last day of the month of interest, leave UTC times to default settings (00:00:00 & 23:59:59). Set Geographic Region to World, click Search beneath Output Options; note the number of earthquakes shown in the top left Search Results window.

question name: How many battle deaths will ACLED record in the Democratic Republic of the Congo in October 2017?
question description: The Armed Conflict Location and Event Dataset (ACLED) summarizes press reports on conflict and protest events in Africa and parts of Asia. Outcome will be determined by the "Realtime [Month of Interest] All Africa File" found on the Realtime Data page (ACLED - http://www.acleddata.com/data/realtime-data/). The count of battle deaths for the period of interest is obtained by summing the 'FATALITIES’ column for events in which the 'COUNTRY’ is the country of interest; 'EVENT_TYPE’ is Battle-Government regains territory, Battle-No change of territory, or Battle-Non-state actor overtakes territory; and 'EVENT_DATE' falls in the period of interest. Question will be resolved when the relevant data is first released.

question name: Before 27 December 2017, will Brazil's Chamber of Deputies vote to send Brazil's President Michel Temer to a Supreme Court or Senate trial?
question description: According to the constitution of Brazil, a two-thirds vote is required for the Chamber of Deputies to authorize a trial by the Supreme Court or the Senate. For more information see  < Title IV, Chapter II, Section III, Article 86 of Brazil's Constitution> http://www.servat.unibe.ch/icl/br00000_.html. After surviving a Chamber of Deputies vote on authorization of a Supreme Court trial in August 2017, Brazilian President Michel Temer faces a new set of corruption charges (http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-41275822, https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-politics/new-brazil-graft-charge-may-be-tougher-for-temer-to-stop-maia-idUSKCN1BF22V, https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-04/cost-of-loyalty-rises-for-brazil-s-temer-ahead-of-new-charges, http://www.latimes.com/world/mexico-americas/la-fg-brazil-temer-20170802-story.html).

question name: Before 27 December 2017, will Poland, Estonia, Latvia, or Lithuania accuse Russia of intervening militarily in its territory without permission?
question description: If the relevant governments are overthrown during an invasion, an announcement by a third party government accusing Russia of invasion will count. Examples of past accusations of Russian military intervention include Georgia's claim that Russia invaded its territory in August of 2008 (http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/world-news/georgia-russia-has-invaded-and-we-are-under-attack-28470695.html), Ukraine's claim the Russia invaded Crimea in February 2014 (https://sputniknews.com/russia/20140228187963690-Ukraine-Accuses-Russian-Soldiers-in-Crimea-of-Invasion-Update1/), Ukraine's condemnation of illegal Russian fighters in Eastern Ukraine in June 2014 (http://mfa.gov.ua/en/press-center/comments/1767-zajava-mzs-ukrajini-pro-chergovi-napadi-bojovikiv-na-skhodi-derzhavi), and Ukraine's statement in August 2014 that Russia military forces had crossed the border and were actively engaged in fighting (https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/aug/28/ukraine-accuses-russia-invading-south-east-help-rebels).

question name: Between 18 December and 28 December 2017, will any World War II Soviet monuments be taken down in Poland?
question description: Poland's president has approved amendments to a law that bans the promotion of communism, including World War II era memorials dedicated to Soviet troops (https://www.rferl.org/a/28778037.html, http://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2017/07/20/russia-preparing-retaliation-against-poland-over-war-memorial-row--agencies/).  Russia has threatened to retaliate against Poland if they remove any of these monuments (http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-40775355, http://www.reuters.com/article/us-russia-poland-sanctions-idUSKBN1A41VB).  If a World War II Soviet monument is taken down (e.g. http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-36656226) the question will close as yes regardless of who takes it down.

question name: Before 29 December 2017, will it be announced that Chinese troops are deploying to the disputed border region between Eritrea and Djibouti?
question description:
As aggression escalates in the Djibouti-Eritrea conflict over the Dumeria Mountain and Island, China has offered to assist in mediation or peacekeeping if requested (http://venturesafrica.com/heres-how-the-international-community-reacts-to-the-eritrea-djibouti-border-dispute/
https://www.yahoo.com/news/china-consider-sending-troops-djibouti-eritrea-135732328.html, http://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy-defence/article/2103947/china-offers-mediate-djibouti-eritrea-border-row-it, http://www.news.com.au/world/africa/tiny-african-country-becomes-playground-for-world-super-powers/news-story/0fa72ddc2df6efc9ac437d8681977fd6).
Deployment of Chinese troops as part of a multinational force would count.

question name: Will the "comfort women" statue be removed from outside the Japanese Consulate in Busan before 1 January 2018?
question description: The "comfort women" statue in front of the Japanese Consulate in Busan, erected in December 2016, was opposed by Japan as a violation of the 2015 agreement settling the issue (http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/05/asia/south-korea-comfort-women-statue/, https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/06/world/asia/japan-south-korea-ambassador-comfort-woman-statue.html). question description: FluNet ( http://www.who.int/influenza/gisrs_laboratory/flunet/en/) is the World Health Organization's global web-based tool for influenza virological surveillance. Relevant data can be accessed via FluNet functions, 'Download influenza laboratory surveillance data from any week' at: http://apps.who.int/flumart/Default?ReportNo=12. Select by: 'Country, area or territory'; Filter by: the country of interest; set the time period to cover the epidemiological-week(s) of interest; and then click 'Display report.' This question will be resolved using the value or sum of values reported in ‘Total number of influenza positive viruses’ or ‘ALL_INF’ for all reporting weeks within the period of interest. Question will be suspended on the last day of the period of interest and resolved when data for the period of interest is released.

question name: Before 21 November 2017, will Nnamdi Kanu, leader of Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), be found?
question description: Nnamdi Kanu is the leader of the IPOB separatist movement in Nigeria, but has not been seen (http://www.dw.com/en/nigeria-pro-biafra-leader-nnamdi-kanu-missing-as-trial-resumes/a-40999227) in public since soldiers allegedly invaded his home in mid-September. A trial against him <http://www.dw.com/en/nigeria-pro-biafra-leader-nnamdi-kanu-missing-as-trial-resumes/a-40999227> has been adjourned to allow more time to ascertain his whereabouts http://www.newsweek.com/war-nigeria-biafra-nnamdi-kanu-686961. Secessionist (https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-15/eastern-nigeria-tensions-rise-over-demands-for-independent-state) sentiment (https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/08/world/africa/nigeria-cameroon-secession-separatists.html) is on the rise in the southeastern part of the country. Kanu's condition when found will not affect the resolution of this question.

question name: Which parties, from among the Green Party, the FDP, and the Left, will be part of Germany's next governing coalition?
question description: Recent elections in Germany have changed the make-up of the Bundestag (http://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/europe/merkel-german-election-coalition-choices/index.html) and Angela Merkel's CDU party is searching for new partners to form a governing coalition (https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2017/09/25/building-a-new-german-coalition-government-wont-be-easy-heres-why/, https://www.reuters.com/article/us-germany-politics/climate-migration-disputes-cloud-german-coalition-talks-idUSKBN1CX0JT, https://www.reuters.com/article/us-germany-politics/german-parties-start-to-find-common-ground-in-coalition-talks-idUSKBN1CZ0XT). If no governing coalition is formed and a new election is held, the question will close as "None of the above").
answer name: The Left Party and the Green Party, but not the FDP

question name: How many cases of MERS-CoV in humans will EMPRES-i record in Saudi Arabia between 1 December 2017 and 15 December 2017?
question description: EMPRES Global Animal Disease Information System (EMPRES-i) is the Food and Agricultural Organization (FAO) of the United Nation's global web-based tool for animal disease surveillance. To access the data from http://empres-i.fao.org: click on the map; click Advanced Search in the top right corner; set OBSERVATION DATES to cover the relevant time period, check MERS-CoV from DISEASE LIST; check Saudi Arabia under Asia from ADMINISTRATIVE UNITS; check human from ANIMALS AFFECTED; click Find; then export to CSV. Outcome will be determined by the sum of the values reported in the "humansAffected" column. Question will be suspended on the last day of the period of interest and resolved based on data posted 15 days from the end of the period.

question name: What will be the approval rate for Japan's cabinet in NHK's monthly survey in December 2017?
question description: This question will be resolved using the approval rate reported for the time of interest on Nippon Hōsō Kyōkai (NHK)'s website (https://www.nhk.or.jp/bunken/research/yoron/political/2017.html). The cabinet approval rate is reported as 支持する ("Support to”) in the first table 内閣：安倍内閣 (“Cabinet: Abe Cabinet”) on that page. The question will be resolved using Google Translate services. Months are indicated by their corresponding number (e.g. 1月 = January). If NHK conducts more than one survey in a month, question resolution will be based on the first set of results posted.

question name: What will be the short-term interest rate for South Africa (ZAF) in December 2017?
question description: This question will be resolved using monthly data reported by the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD - https://data.oecd.org/interest/short-term-interest-rates.htm). Data is retrievable on the 'Short-term interest rates' table on the web site. The relevant country can be found in the HIGHLIGHTED COUNTRIES or LOCATION field, and the relevant time period can be found in the TIME field. Values will be rounded to the nearest one-hundredth. Question will be resolved when the data is released, likely the month after the period of interest.

question name: Will the PITF Worldwide Atrocities Dataset record an event perpetrated by a non-state actor in Ethiopia (ETH) that starts between 29 November 2017 and 13 December 2017?
question description: The question will resolve as "yes" if the Political Instability Task Force (PITF) Worldwide Atrocities Dataset (http://eventdata.parusanalytics.com/data.dir/atrocities.html) records any event with a start date (Start Day, Start Month, Start Year) in the period of interest, inclusive, for which 'Event Location: Country' is the country of interest, and 'Perpetrators: Perp State Role' is: Multiple Perpetrators (Non-State); Non-State, Internal, No State Sanction; Transnational, Non-State; or Unknown/Unclear/Other. Question will be suspended on the last day of the period of interest and resolved when the data is released, typically in the middle of the next month via the .zip file which covers the period of interest. If a qualifying event is recorded, the question will be closed retroactively with the date of the first event as the end date of the question.

question name: Will Catalan pro-independence parties hold a majority of seats after the upcoming regional elections?
question description: Examples of current and past pro-independence parties include the Catalan European Democratic Party (PDECat), the Republican Left of Catalonia (ERC),  the Popular Unity Candidacy (CUP),  Catalonia Yes (CatSi), and Democrats of Catalonia (DC).Regional elections are scheduled for 21 December 2017 (https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/27/world/europe/spain-catalonia-puigdemont.html, http://www.reuters.com/article/us-spain-politics-catalonia/sacked-catalonia-leader-turns-himself-in-polls-show-independence-strength-idUSKBN1D50CS).

question name: Will Barnaby Joyce win the upcoming by-election in New England, Australia?
question description: Australia's former Deputy Prime Minister Barnaby Joyce is running in a by-election scheduled for 2 December 2017, a race which may determine which party holds the majority in Australia's House of Representatives (https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/26/world/australia/citizenship-ruling.html, http://www.northerndailyleader.com.au/story/5021322/whos-in-out-and-on-the-fence-for-the-new-england-by-election/).

question name: Will Iran launch a medium,  intermediate, or intercontinental range ballistic missile or a satellite between 29 November 2017 and 29 December 2017?
question description: The Trump administration declined to certify the Iranian nuclear deal, citing concerns about Iran's missile program (https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2017/10/iran-deal-trump-next/542379/, https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-missiles-diplomacy/iran-open-to-talks-over-its-ballistic-missile-programme-sources-idUSKBN1CB22P).  Examples of previous launches include the September 2017 and March 2016 ballistic missile tests (http://www.cnn.com/2017/09/23/middleeast/iran-ballistic-missile-test/index.html, http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-35752974 ) and the July 2017 satellite launch (https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-satellite/u-s-says-iran-rocket-test-breaches-u-n-resolution-idUSKBN1AC1YY).  For more information on ballistic missiles of various ranges see https://www.armscontrol.org/factsheets/missiles.

question name: Before 1 January 2018, will a Chinese government entity or state owned enterprise take a stake in Youku Tudou, Tencent, or Weibo?
question description: China has proposed investing in web giants Tencent Holdings Ltd, Weibo Corp, and Youku Tudou, a platform owned by Alibaba Group Holding (https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-pushes-for-a-direct-hand-in-chinas-big-tech-firms-1507758314, https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-wants-to-own-small-stake-in-web-firms-1461781500).
clarification 3: Additional references can be found at: : https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/13/business/china-online-stakes-control.html?_r=0, https://www.dealstreetasia.com/stories/chinese-government-eyes-board-seats-in-local-tech-giants-including-tencent-84046/

question name: Between 29 November 2017 and 29 December 2017, will Libya's Sharara oil field experience a production shutdown?
question description: Libya's Sharara oil field, the country's largest, has been beset by production shutdowns (http://english.alarabiya.net/en/business/energy/2017/09/06/Production-restarting-at-Libya-s-Sharara-oilfield-after-blockade-lifted.html, https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-oil/libyas-sharara-oilfield-reopens-after-two-day-shutdown-noc-idUSKCN1C91HX, https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-27/libya-oil-output-gains-as-country-faces-calls-to-join-opec-cuts).

question name: Will the UN Security Council adopt a resolution concerning Somalia between 29 November 2017 and 22 December 2017 ?
question description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the United Nations Security Council (UNSC) adopts a resolution during the period of interest in which the country/region of interest appears in the short description in the Security Council Resolution table (http://www.un.org/en/sc/documents/resolutions/2017.shtml) and/or is mentioned within the adopted resolution itself.

question name: Before 1 January 2018, will South Korea file a World Trade Organization dispute against the United States related to solar panels?
question description: South Korea has threatened to file a WTO complaint if the US imposes additional tariffs or import restrictions on solar panels (http://www.reuters.com/article/us-southkorea-trade-solar/south-korea-may-consider-filing-wto-complaint-over-u-s-solar-tariffs-idUSKBN1D2115; https://www.forbes.com/sites/energysource/2017/11/07/dark-skies-for-american-solar-power-itc-recommends-china-tariffs-in-suniva-trade-case/). For more information on the dispute settlement process see: https://www.wto.org/english/tratop_e/dispu_e/dispu_e.htm.

question name: Will the WHO confirm more than 10 cases of Marburg in 2017?
question description: There have been confirmed cases of Marburg, a deadly virus similar to Ebola, for the first time since 2014 (http://www.who.int/csr/don/15-november-2017-marburg-uganda-kenya/en/, http://time.com/5013603/what-is-marburg-virus/, http://www.cnn.com/2017/10/31/health/marburg-virus-uganda/index.html). Question will be resolved based on the latest WHO data available on 31 December 2017 (http://www.who.int/csr/don/archive/disease/marburg_virus_disease/en/).

question name: Will the UN Security Council adopt a resolution concerning Myanmar by 31 December 2017?
question description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the United Nations Security Council (UNSC) adopts a resolution during the period of interest in which the country/region of interest appears in the short description in the Security Council Resolution table (http://www.un.org/en/sc/documents/resolutions/2017.shtml) and/or is mentioned within the adopted resolution itself.

question name: Will the location of the missing Argentinian submarine be determined before 8 December 2017?
question description: On November 23, 2017, the Argentinian Navy confirmed that its missing submarine, the San Juan, had experienced an explosion near the location of its last contact. (http://www.latimes.com/world/mexico-americas/la-fg-argentina-missing-submarine-20171123-story.html ; https://www.reuters.com/article/us-argentina-submarine/water-entered-missing-argentine-subs-snorkel-causing-short-circuit-idUSKBN1DR2B3?il=0) Question will resolve as "yes" if (a) credible media report that the ship or some remains of the ship have been located OR (b) there is an announcement or confirmation by the Argentinian government that the ship or some remains of the ship have been located.

question name: Before 31 December 2017, will the media report that former Lebanese Prime Minister Saad Hariri has done any of the following: resigned, left the country, disappeared, or become incapacitated?
question description: On November 4, 2017, Lebanese Prime Minister Saad Haririr unexpectedly announced his resignation while he was in the Saudi capital, Riyadh, leading to speculation that Saudi Arabia was forcing him to quit. On November 22, 2017, upon his return to Lebanon, he announced the postponement of his resignation (https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/22/world/middleeast/lebanon-saad-hariri-resignation.html ; https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/25/world/middleeast/lebanon-saad-hariri-iran-saudi-arabia.html?mtrref=www.google.com). Question will resolve as “yes” if credible media or government announcements report that any of the following has happened to Hariri prior to the resolution date: (a) death or medical hospitalization; (b) arrest or detainment; (c) fleeing the country (vs. official travel); OR (d) disappearance.

question name: Will an individual hack of Bitcoin resulting in the theft of $10,000,000 USD or more occur in December 2017?
question description: On November 21, 2017, the company behind the Bitcoin cryptocurrency "tether" announced a hack resulting in a theft valued at $31,000,000 USD that was widely reported in the media (https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-11-21/bitcoin-falls-after-31-million-theft-of-cryptocurrency-tether ; https://www.cnbc.com/2017/11/21/bitcoin-rebounds-to-all-time-high-shrugs-off-cryptocurrency-hack.html). The question will resolve as "yes" if a credible media outlet (e.g., Bloomberg, Reuters) reports an additional, separate Bitcoin hacking event valued at $10,000,000 or more during the period of interest.

question name: Will a lethal confrontation involving national military forces of Saudi Arabia and Iran result in at least one fatality for either side in December 2017?
question description: Tensions between Saudi Arabia and Iran over control of the Middle East have intensified. Some wonder if they will engage in military aggression against each other (http://www.newsweek.com/saudi-arabia-iran-conflict-ballistic-missile-yemen-war-702913 ; https://www.cnbc.com/2017/11/22/could-saudi-arabia-and-iran-really-go-to-war.html ; https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/06/world/middleeast/yemen-saudi-iran-missile.html). Question will resolve as "yes" if a credible media outlet (e.g., Bloomberg, Reuters) reports at least one death (government or civilian) from an attack originating directly from either country. Deaths that result from a proxy war would not count.

question name: Will Great Britain announce a second referendum on Brexit by 31 December 2017?
question description: Some CEO's and Government officials have begun to call for a second referendum on Brexit (http://www.spiegel.de/international/europe/anti-brexit-momentum-gaining-in-britain-a-1179590.html https://www.ft.com/content/2b7c4192-d04d-11e7-9dbb-291a884dd8c6 ; https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/nov/16/goldman-sachs-boss-calls-for-second-brexit-referendum ; https://www.express.co.uk/news/politics/880409/Brexit-second-EU-referendum-Theresa-May-Katarina-Barley-Germany ; http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/09/gordon-brown-urges-jeremy-corbyn-back-second-eu-referendum-brexit/). Question will resolve as "yes" if a credible media outlet (e.g., Bloomberg, Reuters) reports that an official decision to hold a second referendum has been made.

question name: Will a framework for an end to the Syrian conflict be agreed upon by 31 December 2017?
question description: Leaders of Russia, Turkey, and Iran are sponsoring a conference aimed at achieving a peaceful settlement of the Syrian civil war (https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/22/world/europe/russia-turkey-iran-syria-war-peace-talks.html ; http://english.alarabiya.net/en/views/news/middle-east/2017/11/24/Sochi-Summit-Is-the-Syrian-crisis-nearing-resolution-.html ; https://thewire.in/199437/end-syria-war-nears-end-sochi-meeting-unites-iran-russia-turkey/). The question will resolve as "yes" if a credible media source (e.g., Bloomberg, Reuters) reports that Syria has agreed to a framework outlining the future structure of the state that includes BOTH the adoption of a new constitution AND holding elections under United Nations supervision.

question name: Will the European Union announce the imposition of a travel ban or seizure of assets of a Venezuelan government official between 30 November and 31 December?
question description: On November 13, 2017, foreign ministers of the European Union (EU) established the legal basis for imposing sanctions on Venezuelan government officials in order to pressure the Venezuelan government to strengthen the rule of law and legitimate democratic elections (https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/13/world/americas/venezuela-embargo-european-union.html?rref=collection%2Ftimestopic%2FVenezuela&action=click&contentCollection=world&region=stream&module=stream_unit&version=latest&contentPlacement=4&pgtype=collection). Question will resolve as “yes” if credible media or the EU report that the EU is imposing a travel ban or seizing the assets of a Venezuelan government official, including but not limited to President Maduro, during the relevant time period.

question name: Will there be any single day in December 2017 during which 15 or more Ukrainian military personnel are killed?
question description: On November 23, 2017, five (5) Ukrainian servicemen were killed in a military clash (https://frontnews.eu/news/en/18177/Death-of-Ukrainian-military-in-Donbas-is-another-proof-of-tragic-consequences-of-Russian-aggression-Tusk).  Question will resolve as "yes" if credible media report that 15 or more Ukrainian military personnel (to include contractors or civilian employees of the military) were killed on any single day in December 2017.

question name: Will the new Zimbabwean government offer opposition leader Morgan Tsvangirai or ex-Finance Minister Tendai Biti a position in the post-coup government cabinet before 31 December 2017?
question description: Former Prime Minister Tsvangirai returned to Zimbabwe after President Mugabe was put under house arrest (http://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-19883387 ; https://www.express.co.uk/news/world/882008/Morgan-Tsvangirai-who-is-Prime-Minister-Zimbabwe-Robert-Mugabe-opposition-leader-MDC). Former Finance Minister Tendai Biti has discussed means of improving the economy under the new government (https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/south-africa-would-suffer-the-effects-of-zimbabwes-implosion-tendai-biti-20171123). Question will resolve as "yes" if the new Zimbabwean government announces or confirms media reports that either Morgan Tsvangirai or Tendai Biti was offered a position in the new Zimbabwean cabinet.

question name: How many positive influenza virus detections will FluNet record for Brazil between 26 February and 4 March 2018, (epidemiological week 9)?
question description: FluNet ( http://www.who.int/influenza/gisrs_laboratory/flunet/en/) is the World Health Organization's global web-based tool for influenza virological surveillance. Relevant data can be accessed via FluNet functions, 'Download influenza laboratory surveillance data from any week' at: http://apps.who.int/flumart/Default?ReportNo=12. Select by: 'Country, area or territory'; Filter by: 'Country of interest', Year from: '2018', Week: '1', Year to: '2018' Week: '9', and then click 'Display Report.' This question will be resolved by using the sum of values reported in the ‘Total number of influenza positive viruses’ (or .csv ‘ALL_INF’) column for the country of interest for all reporting weeks within the period of interest. Question will be suspended on the last day of the period of interest and resolved when data for the period of interest is released.

question name: Before 15 April 2018, will a sovereign nation launch a ballistic missile at North Korea?
question description: The North Korean ballistic missile launches during the summer of 2017 led to increased tensions with neighboring East Asian countries and the United States, prompting threats of preemptive missile strikes (https://www.militarytimes.com/flashpoints/2017/09/02/north-korea-missile-fear-sets-pre-emptive-strike-debate-in-japan/ ; https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2017/08/north-korea-second-missile-test/535737/ ; https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/checkpoint/wp/2017/08/10/if-trump-wants-a-nuclear-attack-against-north-korea-his-military-advisers-have-few-other-options/?utm_term=.bbf1109aab23). Question will resolve as ““Yes, and the missile struck within the country’s borders”, if credible news media report that a nation state successfully launched a ballistic missile at the country of interest and the missile struck within its borders. Question will resolve as “Yes, and the missile’s flight path was interrupted or went astray” if credible news media report that a nation state launched a missile at the country of interest but was unsuccessful due to either a malfunction or to antiballistic defense mechanisms successfully preventing the missile from reaching its intended target.
answer name: Yes, and the missile struck within North Korea’s borders

question name: How many positive influenza virus detections will FluNet record for China between 12 March 2018 and 18 March 2018 (epidemiological week 11)?
question description: FluNet ( http://www.who.int/influenza/gisrs_laboratory/flunet/en/) is the World Health Organization's global web-based tool for influenza virological surveillance. Relevant data can be accessed via FluNet functions, 'Download influenza laboratory surveillance data from any week' at: http://apps.who.int/flumart/Default?ReportNo=12. Select by: 'Country, area or territory'; Filter by: 'Country of interest', Year from: '2018', Week: '1', Year to: '2018' Week: '53', and then click 'Display report.' This question will be resolved by using the sum of values reported in the ‘Total number of influenza positive viruses’ (or .csv ‘ALL_INF’) column for the country of interest for all reporting weeks within the period of interest. Question will be suspended on the last day of the period of interest and resolved when data for the period of interest is released.
clarification 3: Due to recent volatile data revisions, this question will be resolved four weeks after close based on data available at the end of epidemiological week 15 (15 April 2018).

question name: How many material conflict events involving Occupied Palestinian Territory will ICEWS record in March 2018?
question description: This question will be resolved using event data collected by the Worldwide Integrated Conflict Early Warning System (W-ICEWS or simply ICEWS - https://www.lockheedmartin.com/us/products/W-ICEWS.html), which can be accessed here: https://github.com/gfchallenge/gfc/tree/master/data/ICEWS.  The files entitled Events_YYYY-MM_Factiva.csv contain events that occurred in month MM of year YYYY, whereas the files entitled ReleaseXXX_Factiva.csv each contain a few weeks’ worth of events, spanning the end of 2015 (Release 272) to the present. ICEWS event data are extracted from the Factiva news database, which draws from a multilingual roster of over 6,000 news sources from around the world. These event data are then assigned event type codes based on the Conflict Events and Mediation Observations (CAMEO) event coding ontology (see http://eventdata.parusanalytics.com/cameo.dir/CAMEO.Manual.1.1b3.pdf).This question will be resolved by counting the number of event records for which: 'Event.Date' falls in the period of interest; 'CAMEO code' is three digits equal to: 14x, 15x, 17x, 18x, 19x, 20x, or four digits equal to: 14xx, 15xx, 17xx, 18xx, 19xx, 20xx (where x=any number); and 'Country' is the country of interest.

question name: Will the UN Security Council adopt more than one resolution concerning the Democratic People's Republic of Korea between 8 March 2018 and 31 May 2018?
question description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the United Nations Security Council (UNSC) adopts more than one resolution during the period of interest in which the country/region of interest appears in the short description in the Security Council Resolution table (http://www.un.org/en/sc/documents/resolutions/2018.shtml) and/or is mentioned within the adopted resolution itself.
clarification 3: A passed resolution extending the mandate of the Panel of Experts would count toward the total number of UNSC resolutions on North Korea.

question name: Will a FARC candidate win a seat in the Colombian Senate or House of Representatives in the upcoming legislative elections?
question description: Legislative elections are scheduled for March 11, 2018. The Colombian peace agreement with the guerrilla rebel movement ensures that former members will be able to vote and run as candidates for the legislature and president. It also guarantees that Fuerza Alternativa Revolucionaria del Común (FARC) will hold a minimum of five seats in both the Senate and House. If FARC does not win enough seats in the election then they will be granted the requisite number of seats in the 2018–2022 session (https://www.cnn.com/2017/04/28/americas/colombia-farc-senate/index.html). question description: Any issuer rating will count (e.g., short-term, long-term, foreign currency, local currency, preliminary, or final). question name: Before 8 September 2018, will Saudi Arabia announce that it is ending the blockade of Yemen's Hudaydah port?
question description: Temporary lifting of the blockade or partial lifting of the blockade for specific purposes (e.g., humanitarian aid) is not sufficient to close the question. In November 2017, Saudi Arabia and its allies imposed a blockade on Yemen (US News, NY Times). This included the Houthi-controlled Hudaydah port, which accounted for a majority of commercial imports to the country (ReliefWeb). Saudi Arabia announced it would temporarily ease the blockade but not end it (The Guardian, ReliefWeb, Vice News).

question name: Will the Council of the European Union make an Article 7.1 determination against a member state before 8 September 2018?
question description: Article 7.1 enables the Council of the European Union, acting by a majority of four fifths of its members after obtaining the consent of the European Parliament, to determine whether a member state's actions risk a serious breach of the values referred to in Article 2 of the Treaty of the European Union (EUR-Lex, Politico). In December 2017 the European Commission asked the European Council to consider an Article 7.1 determination against Poland, and some Members of the European Parliament are looking into Hungary (European Commission, Deutsche Welle, European Parliament).

question description: This question will be resolved using event data collected by the Worldwide Integrated Conflict Early Warning System (ICEWS) ICEWS counts are best viewed as a dynamic index of news coverage for a given event/country pair and are most informative when considered in relation to past values for the same country and code(s). ICEWS event data are extracted from the Factiva news database, which draws from a multilingual roster of over 6,000 news sources from around the world. These event data are then assigned event type codes (such as 1411 – “Demonstrate or rally for leadership change”) based on the Conflict Events and Mediation Observations (CAMEO) event codebook. ICEWS times series data: * Filtered ICEWS data: protest events for all countries * Unfiltered ICEWS data This question will be resolved by counting the event records for which: - ‘Event.Date’ is in the period of interest; - ‘CAMEO code’ is three digits equal to 14x or four digits equal to 14xx (where x=any number 0-9); - ‘Country’ is country of interest.

question name: How many positive influenza virus detections will FluNet record for Australia between 30 July 2018 and 19 August 2018 (epidemiological weeks 31-33, inclusive)?
question description: FluNet is the World Health Organization's global web-based tool for influenza virological surveillance. To access relevant data at http://apps.who.int/flumart/Default?ReportNo=12 make the following selections:- Select by: 'Country, area or territory'; - Filter by: Country of interest, - Year from: '2018', Week from: '1', - Year to: '2018' Week to: '53', - Click 'Display report.' This question will be resolved by using the sum of values reported in the ‘Total number of influenza positive viruses’ (or .csv ‘ALL_INF’) column for the country of interest for all reporting weeks within the period of interest. This question will be resolved by consulting the source between 10:00 AM and 4:00 PM ET starting on 24 September 2018 and each Monday thereafter until data are posted. Resolution will be based on the value observed at the time of source consultation.

question name: Will Pakistan execute or be targeted in an acknowledged national military attack before 1 August 2018?
question description: "Acknowledged” means the government of the country executing the attack claims responsibility for it. A “national military attack” includes the employment of conventional or unconventional weapons by one country’s national military forces on another country’s military, military assets, or territory, including citizens located within that territory, but excluding territorial waters, foreign missions, and/or exclusive economic zones. A “cyber” attack will not qualify as a “national military attack.” Attacks by specific military or paramilitary units or non-state actors will not qualify as “national military attacks” unless the government claims responsibility for them.

question description: A “significant leadership disruption” includes confirmed reports that the leader: has resigned, has formally left office, has been forcibly removed from office for 10 or more consecutive days, has fled or been exiled from office for 10 or more consecutive days, has died, has been medically incapacitated or hospitalized for 10 or more consecutive days, or his/her whereabouts have been unknown for 10 or more consecutive days.

question name: Will Iran execute or be targeted in an acknowledged national military attack outside of Syria involving Israel or any G7 nation between 23 August and 7 September 2018?
question description: "Acknowledged” means the government of the country executing the attack claims responsibility for it. A “national military attack” includes the employment of conventional or unconventional weapons by one country’s national military forces on another country’s military, military assets, or territory, including citizens located within that territory, but excluding territorial waters, foreign missions, and/or exclusive economic zones. A “cyber” attack will not qualify as a “national military attack.” Attacks by specific military or paramilitary units or non-state actors will not qualify as “national military attacks” unless the government claims responsibility for them.
